<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-10-0185 </DOCNO><TEXT>A general approach to fluidized bed combustion (FBC) in the 40,000 lb/hrsize is outlined. Three different plants currently in the planning stageare discussed. These are a plant combining FBC with a condensing turbine,a plant combining FBC with a non-condensing turbine and a FBC plant withno cogeneration. Process specifications, cost estimates and economicanalyses for the three projects are given. Environmental regulationsare also considered. 5 figs.</TEXT></DOC>